      <h1 class="book">privacy policy</h1>


<p class="privacy book">Welcome to Dandelion, the intelligent contact book that brings together

everyone you know across multiple networks to create enhanced views of

the people in your life. Use Dandelion to find who you’re looking for, connect

social networks to enhance their information and always have their most

up to date details. Dandelion itself is NOT a social networking service, any

information or notes you add to your contacts on Dandelion is personal to you

and will not be shared with other users.</p>

<p class="privacy book">Dandelion, is a service provided by Bespokd Ltd (Bespokd, Dandelion, we,

our or us) and we take your privacy very seriously. This Privacy Policy covers

our treatment of personally identifiable information (“Personal Information”)

that we collect when you use the Service and describes how that information

may be used, with whom it may be shared, and your choices about such

uses and disclosures. This Privacy Policy does not apply to the practices

of companies that we do not own or control, or to individuals that we do not

employ or manage. We encourage you to read this Privacy Policy carefully

before using the Service. By accessing the Service, you acknowledge and

agree that you have read, fully accept, and will abide by this Privacy Policy.</p>


<p class="privacy book">We may also amend this Privacy Policy from time to time. Your continued

use of the Service after such amendment constitutes your acceptance of

the Privacy Policy as amended. Any capitalized terms used herein without

definition shall have the meaning given to them in the Dandelion Terms of

Use.</p>

<h3 class="book">Information We Collect About You</h3>

<ol class="first">
<li class="book"><strong>Information You Provide to Us.</strong><br>
We receive and store any information you knowingly provide to us.  You can choose not to provide us with certain information, but then you may not be able to register with us or to take advantage of some of our features. For example, in providing the Service, we may collect the following Personal Information from you:

<ol class="second">
<li class="book"><strong>Private personally identifiable information.</strong><br>
The information we collect may include items like your name, e-mail address, telephone number and location-based information (if you agree to provide such information).  Additionally, to register with Dandelion, you may need to provide us with a username and password.</li>
<li class="book"><strong>Third Party Account Information.</strong><br>
Our Service incorporates content from Third Party Websites, such as Facebook, Google, Twitter, LinkedIn and Foursquare.  In order to connect your account on Dandelion to your accounts and contacts on those services (“Third Party Accounts”), we may ask you for account information for those services.   If you provide your Third Party Account credentials to us, you understand that content and/or information in those accounts may be transmitted into your account with us, and that Third Party Account information transmitted to our Website is covered by this Privacy Policy.  We don’t actually store your passwords for those Third Party Accounts.  Instead, we just use an authentication token to verify your user name.</li>
<li class="book"><strong>Information about others.</strong><br>
When you link a Third Party Account to your Dandelion account (by signing in using your Third Party Account information or otherwise), we may collect and store publicly available personal information about your contacts and friends available from those Third Party Websites.  This information may include their photo, name, email address, and interests or other content you have access to when you access such profiles on those Third Party Websites.  You may also be able to invite other users to the Service by providing us with their personal information.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li class="book"><strong>Information Collected Automatically.</strong><br>
We may use various technologies to collect information from your computer or mobile device and about your activities on the Service.

<ol class="second">
<li class="book"><strong>Information collected automatically from your browser.</strong><br>
We may automatically collect information from your browser when you use the Service.  This information includes your IP address, your browser type and language, access times, the content of any undeleted cookies that your browser previously accepted from us (see “Cookies” below), and the referring website address.</li>
<li class="book"><strong>Cookies.</strong><br>
When you use the Service, we may assign your computer or mobile device one or more cookies, to facilitate access to the Service, and to personalize your online experience.  Through the use of cookies, we also may automatically collect information about your activity on the Service, such as the web pages you visit, the links you click, and the searches you conduct.  Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies.</li>
